This paper is about evaluation in Information Retrieval, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses methods for constructing test collections, which involves statistical sampling and active selection of documents, indicating a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new method that places a distribution over systems, which can be seen as a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the human labor involved in constructing test collections, which suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
